            <link>https://www.pbs.org/newshour/show/what-to-know-about-the-latest-push-to-make-daylight-saving-time-permanent</link>
            <description><![CDATA[Congress took its biggest step yet toward ending the twice-yearly changing of the clocks. The House passed the Sunshine Protection Act, which would make daylight saving time permanent nationwide. The bipartisan bill now heads to the Senate, where a similar effort stalled several years ago. Geoff Bennett discussed the push to stop changing the clocks with Scott Yates of the Lock the Clock Alliance.]]></description>
